The Nigeria Customs Service (NCS) has seized 1,553 smuggled items of N17.6 billion Duty Paid Valued (DPV). The seizures were made in the first quarter (Q1) of 2020 across all its commands. NCS Public Relations Officer, Joseph Attah, gave the statistics on Thursday. In January, 465 different contraband items worth N2.5 billion duty were seized. In February, 659 items of DPV at N14.5 billion were confiscated. In March, 429 various seized smuggled items worth N545.8 million were also seized by officers and men of the service. Attah assured that Customs would sustain its anti-smuggling operations and continue to boost non-oil revenue. Meanwhile, the Federal High Court in Abuja has ordered the NCS to pay N5 million damages to a Nigerian, Kehinde Ogunwumiju (SAN). Customs was also ordered to refund an illegal duty Airport officers forced the plaintiff to pay on a laptop bag upon his arrival from a trip. Justice J. T. Tsoho gave the ruling in Suit No: FHC/ABJ/CS/1113/2019. He warned the NCS to stop arbitrary duty imposition and henceforth establish that travellersâ€™ items are for sale before taking actions